#ELLEDigitalCoverStar: With Neena Gupta (@neena_gupta) around, pretence is zero. Nada. As someone who’s lived through multiple iterations of the film landscape, she’s not the one to entertain pressure of any sort. “The earlier ‘Metro’ gave us a solid foundation. That’s not stress, that's an advantage.” Her take on the evolution of women’s stories is grounded. “If our society doesn’t change, our films won’t either. People need to see themselves in characters. Until then, we’ll just keep brushing the surface,” she opines. Click on the 🔗 in the bio to read the interview.
